14/07/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Ambassador to BiH Douglas McElhaney visited Banja Luka on Thursday (13 July) and insisted that the only way to achieve EU and NATO integration is to implement necessary reforms. Meeting with Republika Srpska Prime Minister Milorad Dodik, McElhaney urged acceleration of the reform process, particularly the restructuring of the BiH police sector. 
In other news Thursday, an IMF mission that recently visited BiH presented its conclusions, calling on authorities to speed up structural reforms and resolve the row over the distribution of indirect tax revenues between the entities. The Fund also cited the urgent need for political consensus on the centralisation of banking system supervision.
Also Thursday, the BiH Council of Ministers approved a three-year national strategy for combating terrorism and preventing the financing of terrorist groups. Among other things, the document envisions an action plan by the end of this year. (Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 14/07/06; PBS BiH, RTRS - 13/07/06)
